LAGOS – All-G Entertainment Label is all set to make a difference in the Nigerian music industry. The wave making label which was established in September 10, 2017 officially has two major artists under its umbrella, Kamar Tachio and Riddim. Kamar was the first, followed by Raddim. In a recent interview, the label CEO hinted at his plans to sign in more artistes in 2022 to boost the output of the brand. Tekno Becomes Bitcasino’s New Global Ambassador HAPAwards Celebrate Pasuma, Supports Wakanda-One City Initiative… “All-G Record label, which means “All God Entertainment” intends to sign 2 new artists and churn out new age afro-beats music from them. So far, Kamar has dropped Hajiya Toy Story, an Extended Play (EP), Followed by Guitar and a dream. While Riddim dropped Vibes with the Riddim (EP),” he said. The Label CEO also shed more light on why he signed the two artistes and what he saw in them. “Music has different angles/side that can not be seen by just an artist. We picked two up to be able to give different feel/vibe. We also have plans to sign a female artist very soon.” Speaking on what inspired his idea to kick off a record label, All-G Entertainment Label CEO revealed that music was his best friend while growing up. “Those days, music was what I talked to and found healing in. I was listening to others’ music at the time and I want to be able to do the same for someone out there,” he said.